('93', '1', '2011-11-24 08:30:59', '2011-11-24 08:30:59', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Phuket Information</strong>\r\n\r\nAs Phuket has become more cosmopolitan and grown in population, education on the island has kept apace. Below is a list of preschools, schools, and universities now operating with English-language curriculums on the island.\r\n<p align=\"center\"></p>\r\n<strong>Bilingual Preschool and International Nurseries</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>ABC Nursery-International Childcare Centre </strong>\r\n\r\nA British-owned and managed pre-school, ABC accepts children from 18 months to six years for nursery activities, and run Pre-K classes as well as K1, K2 and K3 levels. They provide lots of creative activities for students such as sing-songs, yoga, and creative artwork. The team consists of three qualified British teachers, each with an assistant, two qualified Thai teachers, a catering team of three and its two British owners <strong>Location</strong>: 59/5 Soi Anna, Sai Yuan Road, T. Rawai\r\n<strong>Tel</strong>: +81 (0) 89-9711813\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>: www.abcnurseryphuket.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Buds Phuket Nursery and Preschool</strong>\r\n\r\nBuds Phuket Nursery and Preschool was a pioneer in bilingual preschool facilities on the island. Buds accepts students between the ages of 18 months and seven years. Class sizes are limited to 12 children per class.\r\n\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: 5/3 Chao Fa Road, Moo 1, T. Chalong (Near Lumpooon Secondhand Store.)\r\n<strong>Tel</strong>: Tel: +66 (0) 76-282232 or +66 (0) 87-2785511\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>: http://www.buds-phuket.com and email: fo@buds-phuket.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Cravens International Nursery Preschool</strong>\r\n\r\nYoungsters can enjoy fun learning experiences including social, physical and art skills at Cravens through prepared activities. Cravens is aimed at children from the ages of 18 months to six years.\r\n\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: 48/5 Moo 10, Soi Jaofa 47 T. Chalong. Turn left at the first 7/11 after HomePro Village, coming from Chalong Circle, Cravens is located about 300m up the soi on the left-hand side.\r\n<strong>Tel</strong>: +66 (0) 76 383150\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>: www.cravensnurseryphuket.com\r\n\r\n<strong>Smiley Kidz Nursery School</strong>\r\n\r\nSmiley Kidz, founded in 2007, is an international nursery, childcare centre, preschool and kindergarten. In their own words: ‚ÄúOur teachers and staff are committed to working within each child\'s comfort zone to ensure optimal social, emotional and educational results.‚Äù Smiley Kidz is located on Kwang Road, connecting the two Chaofa Roads (East and West), roughly halfway between Central Festival Department Store and Chalong. <strong>Location</strong>: 10/28 Moo 3 Jonthong Thani Village, Chaofa Road, Wichit\r\n<strong>Tel</strong>: +81 (0) 84-8470732\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>: http://www.smiley-kidz.com or info@smiley-kids.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>International Schools: Primary and Secondary Schools</h3>\r\n<strong>British International School</strong>\r\n\r\nThe British International School (BIS) is an English medium, co-educational, day and boarding school, set within an extensive purpose-built campus. The 39-acre campus houses world-class facilities which enable students to excel at sports, performance arts as well as in their academic studies.\r\n\r\nThe school was established in 1996 and is home to some 850 students from 18 months to 18 years of age. The student population has over 36 different nationalities represented and is divided into two educational sections; the Primary and Secondary School.\r\n\r\nThe school‚Äôs curriculum is based on the English GCSE and IGCSE programmes which prepare students for entry to the International Baccalaureate Diploma Programme (IB Diploma), an international university entrance qualification, recognised by higher educational institutions in over 100 countries.\r\n\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: 59 Moo 2, Thepkrasattri Rd., Koh Kaew (the road leading to the school is diagonally opposite Royal Phuket Marina)\r\n<strong>Tel</strong>: +66 (0)76-238711-20\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>: http://www.bisphuket.ac.th\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>HeadStart International School Phuket </strong>\r\n\r\nHeadStart International School Phuket offers the British National Curriculum in a global context for students from preschool through to secondary-level. The school welcomes students from different cultural and linguistic backgrounds and values diversity as a key component of the curriculum.\r\n\r\nAll core subjects are taught in English and students take Thai and Mandarin classes each week. The HeadStart curriculum focuses on developing ICT capability from Year 1 and prepares secondary-level students for the IGCSE exams in a variety of subjects. The campus is centrally located in Phuket and has an extensive playground and football pitch on the school grounds.\r\n\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: 41/6 Moo 5, Vichitsongkram Rd., T. Vichit, A. Muang Phuket 83000 (diagonally opposite Makro Self Service.)\r\n<strong>Tel</strong>: +66 (0)76-612876\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>: http://www.headstartphuket.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Phuket International Academy Day School (PIADS) </strong>\r\n\r\nThe Phuket International Academy Day School (PIADS), a non-profit organization, brings a fresh and unique approach to education. It is aspiring to implement all three programmes of the International Baccalaureate (IB) and presently has candidate status for the IB Primary Years Programme, and is applying for candidate status for the IB Middle Years Programme.\r\n\r\nThe choice of this curriculum integrates well with the overall philosophy of the school, and will allow mobile families to easily locate to other countries and have continuity in their child\'s education. Teachers have been recruited internationally for their qualifications and experience. The school caters to students aged three years (kindergarten) to 15 years (grade 8/9) from international and Thai communities. PIADS also has a nursery for children aged from 18 months.\r\n\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: In the foothills of a national park in Thalang on the eastern part of the island.\r\n<strong>Tel</strong>: +66 (0)76-336000\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>: www.phuketinternationalacademy.com or email: info@phuketinternationalacademy.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>QSI International School of Phuket</strong>\r\n\r\nQuality Schools International (QSI) was founded in order to provide a quality education in the English language for expatriates‚Äô children living in the international community. The school accepts students from nursery to grade 12 and follows an American curriculum. Locals who want their children to be educated in English are also accepted.\r\n\r\nThe school recognizes that most of the students might only be enrolled for only two or three years and have diverse educational backgrounds. QSI has 33 schools in 25 countries. In Phuket, the school has more than 100 students. Thai is taught both as a native and a non-native language.\r\n\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: Near Tesco Lotus junction in Phuket Town (the entrance to QSI is next to Wat Samkong on the Bypass Road.)\r\n<strong>Tel</strong>: +66 (0) 76-354077\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>: http://www.qsi.org/pkt_home/pkt_home.htm or email: phuket@qsi.org\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Rawai Progressive International School (aka Montessori School)</strong>\r\n\r\nFounded in 1998, the Rawai Progressive International School is a private school also known by many locals as the Montessori School because of their Montessori educational philosophy. The levels taught here are the Children\'s House Program (or kindergarten) for children aged three to six, lower elementary (ages six-nine), upper elementary (ages nine-12). Montessori is located in Rawai, next to Friendship Beach in the south of the island.\r\n\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: 14/1 M.5 Rawai, Viset Rd., Muang, Phuket\r\n<strong>Tel</strong>: +66 (0)76-289200, +66 (0)76-288281\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>: http://www.montessori-thailand.com or email: admin@montessori-thailand.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Thai schools that offer English and Bilingual programmes</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Darasamuth Phuket School</strong>\r\n\r\nDarasamuth English Programme, part of the Sister Servants of the Immaculate Heart of Mary, was formed during the academic year 2002/2003. The EP operates as a small ‚Äòcommunity‚Äô within the grounds of Darasamuth Phuket School. The school also offers a Mini English Programme (MEP) and offers up-to-date teaching technologies and material and equipment, including a 25-metre swimming pool.\r\n\r\nThey seek to give the students the tools to think for themselves both inside and outside of the classroom setting, whilst maintaining a holistic, child-centred approach to learning. The EP follows the Thai Ministry of Education curriculum requirements in all subject areas, enriched with an additional EP syllabus, as well as field-trip activities outside of the school.\r\n\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: At the Central Festival Department Store‚Äôs intersections in Phuket Town (behind Homeworks.)\r\n<strong>Tel</strong>: +66 (0) 76-212392, +66 (0) 76-235183\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>: www.darasamuth.com or email: darasamuth_p@hotmail.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Kajonkietsuksa School (aka Kajonkiet)</strong>\r\n\r\nA private school established in 1954, Kajonkiet School was the first Thai school in Phuket to have an English programme using the Thai curriculum in 2000. The programme accepts children from pre-K level to primary level (about three to 13 years old). Subjects like English, science and mathematics are taught in English by foreign teachers while Thai and social studies are in Thai. Kajonkiet has expanded to a few more locations around the island including a branch in Paklock Village and one in the Cherngtalay area. The main school is in Phuket Town at Phuket Villa 5 Housing Estate on Chaofa West Road.\r\n\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: 50/6-7 Phuket Villa 5 Village, Chaofa West Road (not far from Central Festival Phuket Department Store)\r\n<strong>Tel</strong>: +66 (0) 76-264770-2\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>: http://www.kajonkietsuksa.ac.th/en/ or email: info@kajonkietsuksa.ac.th\r\n<h4>\r\nWittaya Sathid School</h4>\r\nAlso a private school owned and administered by Supaluck K-Methakul, Ph.D. a native of Phuket who is also known for her charity work with the Childwatch Phuket Formation. The English program at Wittaya Sathid is taught by native speakers and ranges from kindergarten level 1-3 (age three‚Äìfive) and primary level 1-6 (age six‚Äì12.)\r\n\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: 9/2 Komaraphat Road, Phuket Town, near Wachira Hospital.\r\n<strong>Tel</strong>: +66 (0) 76-226028 - 30\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>: http://www.wittayasathid.org or email: wsta@wittayasathid.org\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Thai University offering English-and-Asian-Languages Programme</h3>\r\n<strong>Prince of Songkla University (PSU), Phuket Campus</strong>\r\n\r\nThe PSU Phuket Campus was established in 1993 having sprung from the Phuket Community College (PCC) in Saphan Hin. It later moved to a much bigger site in Kathu. PSU Phuket Campus is very popular as it offers courses with a special emphasis on tourism, including a four-year English-curriculum degree course in hotel management. PSU also offers an International Business in China (IBC) programme and Chinese Studies (CNS). Both programmes use English as the medium of instruction. Chinese is the required second foreign language of the students in the programme.\r\n\r\nIn 2005 a new Bachelor of Arts Programme in Thai Studies, was introduced to Thai and international students. The course is designed to support the preservation of Thai culture.\r\n\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: 80 Moo 1 Vichitsongkram Road, Kathu (near Anuphas Golf Course.)\r\n<strong>Tel</strong>: +66 (0) 76-276200\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>: http://www.fsi.psu.ac.th or fhtcontact@phuket.psu.ac.th\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Did You Know?</strong>\r\n\r\nEducation in Thailand is free if students enroll at government schools and is compulsory for children between the ages of six and 15. After the mandatory schooling time is completed, attendance rates tend to drop up to 50% and only a small percentage of students continue their education beyond secondary school.\r\n\r\nHowever the attendance rate of Thai children at primary school is still very high. Likewise, the attendance rate of Thai school students is roughly 89%, higher than the world average of 79% while Thai highschool students have an attendance rate of 65%, compared to a worldwide average of 51%. Meanwhile, the 41% attendance rate of Thai college students is still considered acceptable when compared with worldwide averages. Children are officially required to receive six years of education, and the government has announced its intention to increase that number to nine years. The literacy rate in Thailand is 94% ‚Äì higher than that of most other countries of Southeast Asia.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Phuket schools ', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'phuket-schools', '', '', '2012-01-04 09:15:52', '2012-01-04 09:15:52', '', '7', 'http://www.genesisvilla.com/?page_id=93', '0', 'page', '', '0'),
